ADD Iteration 2 — Security & Availability

(AIDAP System — Attribute-Driven Design)

Step 1: Review Inputs
Category | Details

---|---
Design Purpose | This is the second refinement iteration of the AIDAP architecture. The goal is to strengthen the system's Security and Availability—two of the highest-priority quality attributes for institutional academic systems.
Primary Functional Requirements | UC5 – Student Authentication, UC2 – Notifications, UC3 – Posting Announcements, UC4 – Viewing Class Analytics
Quality Attributes | Security, Availability
Relevant Constraints | CON-1, CON-3, CON-5
